[{"id":"1","begin":7.2,"end":11.08,"lines":["Imagine not having to put","a limit on yourself,"]},{"id":"2","begin":11.08,"end":12.4,"lines":["based on your need for an income."]},{"id":"3","begin":13.84,"end":16.84,"lines":["Not letting the obligation","that you have to do this or that,"]},{"id":"4","begin":17.36,"end":18.92,"lines":["or you won't have food","to put on the table,"]},{"id":"5","begin":19.64,"end":23.08,"lines":["or a roof over your head,","control your choices."]},{"id":"6","begin":23.08,"end":28.76,"lines":["If you had the basics taken care of,","- food, clothing, shelter, health -"]},{"id":"7","begin":29.44,"end":30.64,"lines":["what would you spend your days doing?"]},{"id":"8","begin":31.48,"end":33.16,"lines":["What's the first thing","that comes to your mind?"]},{"id":"9","begin":35.44,"end":37.16,"lines":["If you want to start a business,"]},{"id":"10","begin":37.16,"end":40.36,"lines":["develop a new idea,","devote yourself to your art,"]},{"id":"11","begin":41.32,"end":43.84,"lines":["or dedicate your life to helping others,"]},{"id":"12","begin":43.84,"end":45.84,"lines":["how much opportunity do you have to do so?"]},{"id":"13","begin":47.24,"end":49.16,"lines":["How much time and energy left over"]},{"id":"14","begin":49.16,"end":51.48,"lines":["after eight hours at work","and two in a commute?"]},{"id":"15","begin":52.88,"end":55.96,"lines":["How much freedom","after bankrupting that business"]},{"id":"16","begin":55.96,"end":57.36,"lines":["you finally took a chance at starting?"]},{"id":"17","begin":58.44,"end":61.36,"lines":["If it fails, that might","very well be the end of it,"]},{"id":"18","begin":62.32,"end":65.52,"lines":["your last chance to live your dream","gone into debt and disillusionment."]},{"id":"19","begin":67.44,"end":72,"lines":["For those of us who have no fallback,","no economic safety net,"]},{"id":"20","begin":72,"end":73.72,"lines":["the stress that gives rise to,"]},{"id":"21","begin":73.72,"end":76.56,"lines":["is a burden we carry with us","in all that we do."]},{"id":"22","begin":77.72,"end":81.4,"lines":["What a difference it could make","if we were able to set that burden down."]},{"id":"23","begin":82.8,"end":84.08,"lines":["What a difference it would make"]},{"id":"24","begin":84.08,"end":87.52,"lines":["if we were able","to take a chance and mess up"]},{"id":"25","begin":87.52,"end":89.52,"lines":["and know that our bills","would still get paid,"]},{"id":"26","begin":90.6,"end":91.96,"lines":["because making mistakes"]},{"id":"27","begin":91.96,"end":93.92,"lines":["is far more valuable","than we give it credit for."]},{"id":"28","begin":94.88,"end":97.24,"lines":["Failure is inherent in all learning."]},{"id":"29","begin":98.12,"end":101.68,"lines":["The path to mastery","is through constant failure"]},{"id":"30","begin":101.68,"end":104.8,"lines":["and constant readjustment","in response to that failure,"]},{"id":"31","begin":104.8,"end":106.88,"lines":["again, and again, and again."]},{"id":"32","begin":108.48,"end":111.88,"lines":["What if all those who failed,","and had to go back to their day jobs,"]},{"id":"33","begin":111.88,"end":115.52,"lines":["had gotten a second, a third, a fourth,","a perpetual chance even."]},{"id":"34","begin":116.28,"end":117.32,"lines":["Where would we be today?"]},{"id":"35","begin":118.6,"end":123.44,"lines":["Cancer cured, flying cars,","a colony on Mars?"]},{"id":"36","begin":125.84,"end":129.64,"lines":["The world that I imagine","as a result of this thought experiment"]},{"id":"37","begin":129.64,"end":131.56,"lines":["is a world that I believe we can reach."]},{"id":"38","begin":132.2,"end":135.68,"lines":["But the only way to reach it","is if people are truly free."]},{"id":"39","begin":136.64,"end":137.44,"lines":["The type of freedom"]},{"id":"40","begin":137.44,"end":141.4,"lines":["that comes from equal opportunities","and the ability to make choices,"]},{"id":"41","begin":141.4,"end":143.4,"lines":["based on not what you have","to do to survive,"]},{"id":"42","begin":143.4,"end":149.2,"lines":["but what you want to do to thrive."]},{"id":"43","begin":149.2,"end":153.08,"lines":["We could do this by providing","a universal basic income to everyone."]},{"id":"44","begin":154,"end":157.88,"lines":["Now, in its simplest form,","the idea of a universal basic income"]},{"id":"45","begin":157.88,"end":161.52,"lines":["means that everyone should receive","an amount of money"]},{"id":"46","begin":161.52,"end":165.48,"lines":["sufficient to make ends meet,","regardless of their circumstances,"]},{"id":"47","begin":166.32,"end":168.88,"lines":["like employment,","social status, or even need."]},{"id":"48","begin":170.12,"end":174.16,"lines":["Then, those who are able,","or wish to supplement their income,"]},{"id":"49","begin":174.16,"end":176.56,"lines":["are then free to take","any work that they choose."]},{"id":"50","begin":176.56,"end":178.72,"lines":["The income they receive from that work"]},{"id":"51","begin":179.28,"end":182.64,"lines":["would be an addition","to their universal basic income,"]},{"id":"52","begin":182.64,"end":183.88,"lines":["- after taxes, of course."]},{"id":"53","begin":184.4,"end":187.04,"lines":["The basic income is unconditional"]},{"id":"54","begin":187.04,"end":190.36,"lines":["in that nothing you do or don't do","will affect you receiving it."]},{"id":"55","begin":190.36,"end":195.96,"lines":["It enshrines the principle","that we are all valued members"]},{"id":"56","begin":195.96,"end":198.72,"lines":["of these human societies","we've created all over the world."]},{"id":"57","begin":198.72,"end":201.76,"lines":["We have a right to share","in their collective wealth."]},{"id":"58","begin":203.84,"end":206.16,"lines":["The philosopher, Thomas Paine,"]},{"id":"59","begin":206.16,"end":209.76,"lines":["in 1797 wrote a pamphlet","called \"Agrarian Justice,\""]},{"id":"60","begin":210.64,"end":213.12,"lines":["where he makes an argument","for universal basic income."]},{"id":"61","begin":214.4,"end":215.04,"lines":["He states that,"]},{"id":"62","begin":215.64,"end":218.56,"lines":["\"The earth in its natural,","uncultivated state"]},{"id":"63","begin":218.56,"end":222.4,"lines":["was and ever would have continued to be","the common property of the human race.\""]},{"id":"64","begin":223.6,"end":224.44,"lines":["He goes on to say,"]},{"id":"65","begin":224.44,"end":228.44,"lines":["\"It is the value of the improvement only","and not of the earth itself"]},{"id":"66","begin":228.44,"end":230.28,"lines":["that is individual property,"]},{"id":"67","begin":230.28,"end":235.52,"lines":["and that the proprietor, therefore,","of cultivated lands,"]},{"id":"68","begin":235.52,"end":239,"lines":["owes to the community a ground rent","for the land which he holds.\""]},{"id":"69","begin":241.12,"end":244.44,"lines":["Now, the idea that we should all receive","a dividend from our stake"]},{"id":"70","begin":244.44,"end":246.92,"lines":["and our shared ownership","of the planet's resources"]},{"id":"71","begin":246.92,"end":251.16,"lines":["is a powerful one,","and an important one for the future."]},{"id":"72","begin":251.92,"end":256.2,"lines":["A future where technological advances","with machine learning and automation"]},{"id":"73","begin":256.2,"end":258.6,"lines":["are poised to greatly","disrupt our societies"]},{"id":"74","begin":258.6,"end":260.56,"lines":["and create an ever deepening inequality."]},{"id":"75","begin":261.44,"end":264.16,"lines":["To counter this, we must find a way"]},{"id":"76","begin":264.16,"end":267.36,"lines":["to sever the connection","between work and income."]},{"id":"77","begin":269.08,"end":273.68,"lines":["I believe that we have","a unique opportunity to do just that,"]},{"id":"78","begin":273.68,"end":275.28,"lines":["and at the same time, do away"]},{"id":"79","begin":275.28,"end":278.52,"lines":["with that very stress","of having to make ends meet"]},{"id":"80","begin":278.52,"end":284.56,"lines":["by working a job that, essentially,","a robot could do better."]},{"id":"81","begin":284.56,"end":289.44,"lines":["A report published by Carl Benedikt Frey","and Michael Osborne of Oxford University"]},{"id":"82","begin":289.44,"end":293.08,"lines":["found that 47 percent of US jobs"]},{"id":"83","begin":293.92,"end":297.44,"lines":["are at risk of automation","in the next decade or two."]},{"id":"84","begin":297.44,"end":300.64,"lines":["In poorer countries like India,","69 percent of jobs are at risk."]},{"id":"85","begin":300.64,"end":302.8,"lines":["In China, 77 percent."]},{"id":"86","begin":303.72,"end":306.04,"lines":["A report published","by the World Economic Forum"]},{"id":"87","begin":306.68,"end":311.36,"lines":["argues that job losses could be offset","by employment growth in other areas,"]},{"id":"88","begin":311.88,"end":313.08,"lines":["but comes to the conclusion"]},{"id":"89","begin":313.6,"end":318.08,"lines":["that the rise of robots will still lead","to a net loss of over five million jobs"]},{"id":"90","begin":318.08,"end":320.4,"lines":["in 15 major developed","and emerging economies,"]},{"id":"91","begin":320.4,"end":321.12,"lines":["by 2020."]},{"id":"92","begin":322.12,"end":325.36,"lines":["These aren't just factory jobs","that we're talking about here."]},{"id":"93","begin":325.36,"end":328.12,"lines":["Those jobs are already mostly gone","in the western world."]},{"id":"94","begin":328.12,"end":331.04,"lines":["We're talking about cashiers,","telemarketers,"]},{"id":"95","begin":331.04,"end":336.04,"lines":["jobs in insurance and the food industry,","serving, office and administrative jobs,"]},{"id":"96","begin":336.04,"end":338.44,"lines":["sales, transportation"]},{"id":"97","begin":338.44,"end":339.4,"lines":["- the list goes on."]},{"id":"98","begin":340.52,"end":342.28,"lines":["The power of machine learning"]},{"id":"99","begin":342.28,"end":345.12,"lines":["means that the jobs people thought","would be safe from automation"]},{"id":"100","begin":345.84,"end":346.84,"lines":["are now at risk too."]},{"id":"101","begin":350.4,"end":354.08,"lines":["Katja Grace from Oxford's","Future of Humanity Institute"]},{"id":"102","begin":354.08,"end":358.76,"lines":["led a study asking the world's leading","researchers in artificial intelligence"]},{"id":"103","begin":358.76,"end":366.52,"lines":["when they think artificial intelligence","will be better than human beings","at a wide range of tasks."]},{"id":"104","begin":368.44,"end":372.56,"lines":["North American researchers estimate","that this will happen in 74 years."]},{"id":"105","begin":373.44,"end":377.04,"lines":["But their Asian counterparts","see this happening in just 30 years."]},{"id":"106","begin":378.36,"end":380.24,"lines":["However you look at it,"]},{"id":"107","begin":381.12,"end":384.92,"lines":["before long AI will outsmart humans","in almost everything."]},{"id":"108","begin":386.24,"end":388.28,"lines":["I think 30 years is a reasonable estimate,"]},{"id":"109","begin":389.04,"end":392.4,"lines":["but there are important factors","in slowing down automation."]},{"id":"110","begin":392.4,"end":394.68,"lines":["One of those is likely","the cheapness of labor."]},{"id":"111","begin":395.44,"end":400.04,"lines":["Think how difficult the fight","for higher wages will be in the future"]},{"id":"112","begin":400.04,"end":404.36,"lines":["where technology offers cheaper and more","efficient results than human labor."]},{"id":"113","begin":405.64,"end":406.68,"lines":["In our current economic model"]},{"id":"114","begin":406.68,"end":411,"lines":["where income, and therefore survival,","is dependent on having a job,"]},{"id":"115","begin":411.56,"end":414.6,"lines":["workers will have","very little leverage to negotiate"]},{"id":"116","begin":414.6,"end":417.52,"lines":["as wages will be driven down","by the constant threat"]},{"id":"117","begin":417.52,"end":420.36,"lines":["of either outsourcing","to a cheaper labor force overseas,"]},{"id":"118","begin":421.32,"end":422.12,"lines":["or to robots."]},{"id":"119","begin":423.92,"end":427.32,"lines":["In our current economic model,","who benefits from automation?"]},{"id":"120","begin":428.32,"end":429.32,"lines":["In the past,"]},{"id":"121","begin":429.32,"end":432,"lines":["the main benefactors","of technological advances"]},{"id":"122","begin":432,"end":433.36,"lines":["have been businesses, industry."]},{"id":"123","begin":434.2,"end":436.72,"lines":["Technology has made","the world richer overall, yes,"]},{"id":"124","begin":437.64,"end":438.92,"lines":["but not everyone has benefited."]},{"id":"125","begin":440.16,"end":445.52,"lines":["In 2009, the top 1 percent","owned 44 percent of the world's wealth."]},{"id":"126","begin":446.4,"end":449.32,"lines":["In 2014, they had 48 percent."]},{"id":"127","begin":449.84,"end":450.84,"lines":["By 2020, it is estimated"]},{"id":"128","begin":450.84,"end":454.88,"lines":["that the 1 percent will own","54 percent of global wealth."]},{"id":"129","begin":456.68,"end":460.04,"lines":["Now, this concentration of wealth,","it doesn't have to continue,"]},{"id":"130","begin":460.04,"end":461.6,"lines":["we can change the system."]},{"id":"131","begin":462.44,"end":466.12,"lines":["For the first time in history,","technology could lead us"]},{"id":"132","begin":466.12,"end":470.32,"lines":["to the abundance necessary","to enrich humanity on an individual level."]},{"id":"133","begin":473.32,"end":474.12,"lines":["To get there,"]},{"id":"134","begin":475.6,"end":479.48,"lines":["we have to be brave and open-minded enough","to dream a better world,"]},{"id":"135","begin":479.48,"end":481.24,"lines":["and then take the steps","towards that world."]},{"id":"136","begin":482.36,"end":486.36,"lines":["Right now, automation is a threat,","but it doesn't have to be."]},{"id":"137","begin":487.48,"end":491.12,"lines":["With a universal basic income,","it could be our road to freedom."]},{"id":"138","begin":494.12,"end":495.24,"lines":["To buy that freedom,"]},{"id":"139","begin":497.2,"end":502.28,"lines":["we need to stop running our economy","on the ideologies of the past"]},{"id":"140","begin":502.28,"end":504.56,"lines":["and start designing","the economy of the future."]},{"id":"141","begin":506.68,"end":508.2,"lines":["Now, there are many ways"]},{"id":"142","begin":508.2,"end":510.16,"lines":["that we could fund","a universal basic income."]},{"id":"143","begin":510.88,"end":512.6,"lines":["Most of them involve taxation reforms"]},{"id":"144","begin":512.6,"end":516.84,"lines":["that are sorely needed in our shifting,","highly technical, globalized economy."]},{"id":"145","begin":519.44,"end":522.24,"lines":["We could, as Thomas Paine suggested,"]},{"id":"146","begin":522.24,"end":525.56,"lines":["start thinking differently","about the private ownership of land,"]},{"id":"147","begin":526.92,"end":529.36,"lines":["or even the resources","that we all need to survive."]},{"id":"148","begin":530.28,"end":531.76,"lines":["We could start thinking differently"]},{"id":"149","begin":531.76,"end":534.4,"lines":["about innovation","and the ownership of ideas,"]},{"id":"150","begin":534.4,"end":538.32,"lines":["or the ownership of data","that we give freely to large corporations"]},{"id":"151","begin":538.32,"end":541.24,"lines":["who then profit from it,"]},{"id":"152","begin":541.24,"end":543.64,"lines":["or the ownership","of technological progress,"]},{"id":"153","begin":543.64,"end":545.2,"lines":["which has been driven","by centuries of interchanging ideas."]},{"id":"154","begin":546.16,"end":550.28,"lines":["Many of the technical wonders","that we enjoy in our everyday lives,"]},{"id":"155","begin":550.28,"end":553.64,"lines":["like computers and smartphones,","are based on research"]},{"id":"156","begin":554.16,"end":557.16,"lines":["that, to some degree,","has been taxpayer funded"]},{"id":"157","begin":557.16,"end":560.4,"lines":["and are produced with resources,","many of them rare minerals,"]},{"id":"158","begin":560.4,"end":562.68,"lines":["that are sourced from","the very ground we all walk."]},{"id":"159","begin":563.8,"end":565.36,"lines":["How should these profits be shared?"]},{"id":"160","begin":568.6,"end":570.2,"lines":["There's also mounting evidence"]},{"id":"161","begin":570.2,"end":573,"lines":["through the many experiments","that have been done"]},{"id":"162","begin":573,"end":575.16,"lines":["with universal basic income","all over the world,"]},{"id":"163","begin":575.16,"end":578.04,"lines":["that the system leads","to lower crime rates,"]},{"id":"164","begin":578.04,"end":580.32,"lines":["lower school dropout rates,"]},{"id":"165","begin":581,"end":583.76,"lines":["fewer accidents","and stress related illnesses,"]},{"id":"166","begin":583.76,"end":587.28,"lines":["whilst increasing the level","of education and entrepreneurship."]},{"id":"167","begin":589.16,"end":590.32,"lines":["These findings,"]},{"id":"168","begin":590.32,"end":592.96,"lines":["along with the removal","of the burdens and bureaucracy"]},{"id":"169","begin":592.96,"end":594.68,"lines":["that comes with our current","welfare system,"]},{"id":"170","begin":595.36,"end":599.32,"lines":["would lead to massive savings","in taxpayer money"]},{"id":"171","begin":599.32,"end":601.88,"lines":["that could be diverted","into funding a universal basic income."]},{"id":"172","begin":604.2,"end":606.12,"lines":["Now, these are just a few ideas."]},{"id":"173","begin":606.96,"end":610.08,"lines":["They may seem implausible","or impossible even,"]},{"id":"174","begin":610.08,"end":612.76,"lines":["but where there's a will,","there's a way, no?"]},{"id":"175","begin":614.88,"end":618.28,"lines":["To better understand","where we are today and how we got here,"]},{"id":"176","begin":618.84,"end":621.96,"lines":["it is important to delve into the past"]},{"id":"177","begin":622.48,"end":626.4,"lines":["and to understand that the systems","that frame our lives"]},{"id":"178","begin":626.4,"end":627.64,"lines":["are man-made."]},{"id":"179","begin":627.64,"end":628.68,"lines":["We can change them."]},{"id":"180","begin":630.84,"end":637,"lines":["Our current man-made system is designed","to reach a goal grounded in ideology"]},{"id":"181","begin":637,"end":640.36,"lines":["that is today at odds","with an equitable and sustainable future."]},{"id":"182","begin":641.08,"end":643.68,"lines":["That goal is maximum growth","of the economy."]},{"id":"183","begin":644.32,"end":647.4,"lines":["In perpetuity, Adam Smith,"]},{"id":"184","begin":647.4,"end":650.32,"lines":["who's been coined","The Father of Modern Capitalism,"]},{"id":"185","begin":650.32,"end":653.72,"lines":["had a clear idea of how to get there,","of how to reach that goal,"]},{"id":"186","begin":654.44,"end":656.28,"lines":["by maximizing worker efficiency"]},{"id":"187","begin":656.28,"end":658.96,"lines":["and as a result,","production and consumption."]},{"id":"188","begin":660.24,"end":664,"lines":["By breaking down complex processes","into many tiny steps,"]},{"id":"189","begin":664,"end":665.6,"lines":["each allotted to one worker,"]},{"id":"190","begin":666.8,"end":671,"lines":["human beings became little more","than cogs in the industrial machine,"]},{"id":"191","begin":671,"end":675.04,"lines":["whose output was an imagined","infinite economic growth."]},{"id":"192","begin":677.4,"end":678.56,"lines":["It's interesting to note"]},{"id":"193","begin":679.2,"end":682.32,"lines":["that Adam Smith himself","pointed out the downfall of a system,"]},{"id":"194","begin":682.32,"end":686.08,"lines":["which in effect, employs human beings","into mindless drudgery"]},{"id":"195","begin":686.08,"end":687.44,"lines":["for half of their working life,"]},{"id":"196","begin":687.44,"end":689.4,"lines":["in order for them to make ends meet."]},{"id":"197","begin":690.32,"end":695,"lines":["He warned that forcing individuals","to perform mundane and repetitive tasks"]},{"id":"198","begin":695,"end":697.64,"lines":["would lead to an ignorant","and dissatisfied workforce."]},{"id":"199","begin":699.48,"end":701.8,"lines":["This was, it seems,","an acceptable side effect,"]},{"id":"200","begin":701.8,"end":705.4,"lines":["as the goal was, after all,","the material wealth of nations"]},{"id":"201","begin":705.4,"end":708.16,"lines":["and not an enlightened","and content population."]},{"id":"202","begin":709.4,"end":715.64,"lines":["Smith, he believed monetary incentives","to be vital to get people to work."]},{"id":"203","begin":717.2,"end":718.88,"lines":["After all, why would anyone choose"]},{"id":"204","begin":718.88,"end":722.16,"lines":["the hard and repetitive toil","that offer in the factories of his day,"]},{"id":"205","begin":722.16,"end":724.92,"lines":["if it wasn't absolutely","necessary for survival?"]},{"id":"206","begin":725.8,"end":727.52,"lines":["The preconception was"]},{"id":"207","begin":727.52,"end":731.48,"lines":["that human beings are, in essence,","lazy and to some degree untrustworthy,"]},{"id":"208","begin":731.48,"end":733.96,"lines":["unless incentivized monetarily","to be otherwise."]},{"id":"209","begin":736.52,"end":741.16,"lines":["The same school of thought","was then applied to our education system,"]},{"id":"210","begin":741.96,"end":746.28,"lines":["where instead of money, exam scores,","and degrees, and certificates"]},{"id":"211","begin":746.28,"end":747.68,"lines":["are used to incentivize learning,"]},{"id":"212","begin":748.76,"end":752.28,"lines":["as well as being pre-requisites","for graduating and then finding a job."]},{"id":"213","begin":752.96,"end":755.6,"lines":["From an early age, we become accustomed"]},{"id":"214","begin":755.6,"end":758.6,"lines":["to working for extrinsic,","rather than intrinsic rewards."]},{"id":"215","begin":759.12,"end":763.88,"lines":["Instead of being motivated","from that feeling of accomplishment,"]},{"id":"216","begin":763.88,"end":767.48,"lines":["when you come to understand concepts","and their application in the world,"]},{"id":"217","begin":767.48,"end":769.8,"lines":["that eureka moment,","when you finally get something."]},{"id":"218","begin":770.72,"end":771.48,"lines":["Instead of that,"]},{"id":"219","begin":772.12,"end":775.04,"lines":["we're motivated to memorize","words and labels,"]},{"id":"220","begin":775.56,"end":780.64,"lines":["repeating them like a parrot,","to pass that exam, get that degree,"]},{"id":"221","begin":781.4,"end":784.64,"lines":["and contribute to that common goal,","endless economic growth."]},{"id":"222","begin":787.2,"end":788.2,"lines":["What's wrong with that?"]},{"id":"223","begin":790.2,"end":792.84,"lines":["Hasn't it served to make","all of our lives a lot more wealthy?"]},{"id":"224","begin":793.88,"end":794.96,"lines":["Yes, it has."]},{"id":"225","begin":794.96,"end":796.64,"lines":["At least, materially it has,"]},{"id":"226","begin":797.72,"end":804.44,"lines":["but it's also led to, as Smith warned,","an uninformed, dissatisfied population"]},{"id":"227","begin":804.44,"end":808.92,"lines":["forever seeking extrinsic validation","and instant gratification."]},{"id":"228","begin":809.64,"end":810.52,"lines":["The perfect consumer."]},{"id":"229","begin":812.96,"end":815.56,"lines":["Pollution of land, sea, and air"]},{"id":"230","begin":815.56,"end":818.56,"lines":["are the other fruits of this","low cost approach to civilization,"]},{"id":"231","begin":819.16,"end":822.2,"lines":["where we consume more","with every passing year,"]},{"id":"232","begin":822.2,"end":824.52,"lines":["as if this planet","were actually expanding in step."]},{"id":"233","begin":826.76,"end":830,"lines":["Many of the conditions","that make this planet beautiful,"]},{"id":"234","begin":830,"end":833.92,"lines":["bountiful, and capable","of sustaining human life"]},{"id":"235","begin":833.92,"end":836.4,"lines":["are facing threats so far gone,"]},{"id":"236","begin":836.4,"end":840.04,"lines":["that our current technology","might not be able to deal with them,"]},{"id":"237","begin":840.04,"end":842.32,"lines":["even if we made","a concerted effort to do so,"]},{"id":"238","begin":842.32,"end":843.44,"lines":["which we are not."]},{"id":"239","begin":845.2,"end":846,"lines":["Despite this,"]},{"id":"240","begin":846.76,"end":851.04,"lines":["our measure for success and well-being","is still Gross Domestic Product."]},{"id":"241","begin":851.04,"end":856.64,"lines":["The amount of stuff we produce","without any regard to actual need,"]},{"id":"242","begin":858.12,"end":860.28,"lines":["making our economic system work"]},{"id":"243","begin":860.28,"end":864.28,"lines":["against the very systems we rely on","for our survival and well-being."]},{"id":"244","begin":866.4,"end":867.92,"lines":["What does this tell us?"]},{"id":"245","begin":869.76,"end":872.84,"lines":["Do we not have to rethink","our very definition of success?"]},{"id":"246","begin":873.76,"end":874.92,"lines":["What makes a nation truly wealthy?"]},{"id":"247","begin":874.92,"end":880.28,"lines":["I believe that to find these answers,"]},{"id":"248","begin":880.28,"end":883.92,"lines":["we have to be willing","to examine our core belief systems"]},{"id":"249","begin":883.92,"end":885.88,"lines":["and ask ourselves if they're serving us."]},{"id":"250","begin":886.8,"end":889.52,"lines":["By us, I mean all of us,"]},{"id":"251","begin":889.52,"end":892,"lines":["because if we're to evolve as a species,"]},{"id":"252","begin":892.68,"end":896,"lines":["we must rise above the individual interest"]},{"id":"253","begin":896,"end":899.16,"lines":["and start looking towards the interest","of the collective, the whole."]},{"id":"254","begin":900.84,"end":903.92,"lines":["Our world is fast changing, and with it,"]},{"id":"255","begin":903.92,"end":908.08,"lines":["the societies and the systems","that we've built to sustain us."]},{"id":"256","begin":908.08,"end":911.44,"lines":["Now, these changes will happen","with or without our participation."]},{"id":"257","begin":911.44,"end":914.04,"lines":["It's not a question of if,","but of when and how."]},{"id":"258","begin":914.04,"end":919.36,"lines":["The how is something","we have a little control over,"]},{"id":"259","begin":919.92,"end":922.12,"lines":["but only to the extent","of how willing we are"]},{"id":"260","begin":922.12,"end":926.12,"lines":["to look at the paths ahead,","understand the inevitable changes we face,"]},{"id":"261","begin":926.12,"end":927.04,"lines":["and to prepare."]},{"id":"262","begin":928.52,"end":929.6,"lines":["We must prepare."]},{"id":"263","begin":932.64,"end":934.52,"lines":["These will be the deciding factors"]},{"id":"264","begin":934.52,"end":938.44,"lines":["and whether a particular change","will be positive or negative for society."]},{"id":"265","begin":939.84,"end":943.76,"lines":["Now, the how might very well be","a universal basic income,"]},{"id":"266","begin":944.32,"end":947.36,"lines":["which has the potential","to both mitigate unemployment,"]},{"id":"267","begin":947.36,"end":951.08,"lines":["greatly accelerate the rate","of technological development,"]},{"id":"268","begin":951.76,"end":953.2,"lines":["possibly save the planet,"]},{"id":"269","begin":953.2,"end":957.16,"lines":["and make people be more fulfilled","and happy than they have ever been."]},{"id":"270","begin":957.16,"end":960.32,"lines":["Now, I think that's worth a shot."]},{"id":"271","begin":961.04,"end":961.36,"lines":["Don't you?"]},{"id":"272","begin":963.24,"end":963.76,"lines":["Thank you."]},{"id":"273","begin":963.76,"end":967.2,"lines":["[applause]"]}]